The paper deals with secure multiparty computation (MPC) and distributed algorithms, which are topics commonly found in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-categories. However, given the focus on secure computation and distributed algorithms, cs.CR and cs.DC are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions load balancing, which could potentially place it in the cs.SY sub-category.
